    {
      "id": "RQ-0014",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Turn RalphMac continuation next steps into native actions",
      "description": "Improve Run Control so machine-provided operator next steps become native actions where safe instead of mostly appearing as terminal instructions. The app should classify each continuation or blocking next step as actionable, copy-only, or unsupported-with-reason, then render buttons for safe actions such as refresh, validate, repair preview, undo list, stop after current, and status refresh.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "ralphmac",
        "ux",
        "continuation",
        "blocking",
        "recovery"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphMac/RunControlDetailSections+Configuration.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+RunnerState.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/WorkspaceRunnerController+Execution.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/",
        "docs/features/app.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`RunControlDetailSections+Configuration.swift` renders many operator next steps as text rows or command strings.",
        "Lock recovery has proper buttons, but other continuation and blocking actions are often informational only.",
        "This makes the native app feel like a log viewer around terminal commands instead of an operator console."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inventory machine continuation and blocking next-step payloads currently surfaced in Run Control.",
        "Define an app-side action classification for safe native actions, copy-command fallbacks, and unsupported actions with reasons.",
        "Add native buttons for refresh, queue validate, repair preview, undo list, stop after current, retry/status refresh, and any other safe existing machine continuation.",
        "Keep terminal command rendering only as a fallback for actions that are intentionally not native.",
        "Add Swift UI/state tests covering at least one blocking state with actionable continuation buttons beyond lock recovery."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "update the .ralph/queue.jsonc with tasks to remediate every finding.",
