        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests/",
        "docs/features/app.md",
        "docs/machine-contract.md",
        "docs/decisions.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`crates/ralph/src/cli/app_parity.rs` tracks broad command parity and test names, but the audit findings are scenario-level behavior gaps.",
        "The current parity shape would not catch loop terminal summary semantics, Stop After Current using a human CLI command, custom queue-path first-load UX, hardcoded worker controls, or text-only continuation next steps.",
        "A coarse parity registry can create false confidence while user-visible CLI/app behavior still drifts."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define scenario-level parity entries for empty loop queue, blocked loop queue, loop runner failure, Stop After Current, custom queue path workspace, plugin runner/native override visibility, configured parallel workers above default menu choices, and continuation next-step actions.",
